The paper deals with the discovery of association rules, which is a task in data management and finds application in artificial intelligence, data mining, and the semantic web. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel approach for the discovery of a specific set of implications, which involves the use of hypergraph dualization algorithm, which has applications in data base theory, artificial intelligence, and game theory. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses an application of the method for analysis of gene expression data related to a particular phenotypic variable, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
